07/09/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Britain's new ambassador to Macedonia, Robert Chatterton Dickson, has praised the progress achieved in defence reforms. 
During a meeting Monday (6 September) with Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski, Dickson said Britain would provide future support to the reform process, stressing that the full implementation of the Ohrid Peace Accords is a key political requirement for Macedonia's EU and NATO bids.
In other news Monday, the government adopted a National Strategy for Integration in the EU. 
The document identifies the long-term priorities related to the endeavour. 
(Utrinski Vesnik, Dnevnik - 07/09/04; Makfax, A1 TV - 06/09/04)
